div.div:
Exclude new routes from CSRF token verification
The CSRF token verification middleware has been updated with new routes. The routes '/login', '/otp', and '/recovery' have been added to the exception array, meaning they will be excluded from CSRF token verification. These changes help to adjust the CSRF token checks to the requirements of the application.

Update theme, language settings, and remove comment in Exception Handler
Updated theme and language settings in turnstile-widgets from fixed values ("light" and "pl") to adapt automatically to user preferences. Also, uncommented a line in the Exception Handler to send email alerts when an application error occurs.

Change language for Accounting UI to English
The commit translates the labels used in the AccountingMain UI from Czech to English. This change affects the display strings in the 'income_ratio' and 'external_expense' sections, to improve clarity and user understanding for English speakers.

Translate application's user interface to Czech
This commit involves changing the language of the user interface from English to Czech. Changes are made in various PHP files, including views, messages, and email templates, to improve user experience for Czech-speaking users.

Translate English text for several views and messages to Czech
This commit updates numerous PHP files to change the system language from English to Czech. It involves adjusting text in views and messages across sales, statistics, validation files, and email templates. Additionally, some error messages and prompts related to passwords have been translated. This change assists to support for Czech language users on the platform.
